# Campus Map - Project Context

Full-stack interactive campus map. Admin uploads a map image, draws building polygons over it in the editor, attaches metadata, and publishes a public read-only view. The app also includes IoT device management overlays (lights, water valves, and one global temp/humidity sensor per map) with MQTT realtime updates plus a programming dashboard for firmware generation and OTA lifecycle management.

## Stack

- **Next.js 16** (App Router, Turbopack) + **TypeScript strict**
- **Tailwind CSS v4** + **shadcn/ui** (`src/components/ui/*`)
- **PostgreSQL** via `pg` (parameterized queries, JSONB for polygon points)
- **NextAuth v5** (Credentials, JWT, Edge-safe middleware - see `auth.mdc`)
- **Zustand** for editor state (`src/stores/editor-store.ts`)
- **Zod** for validation (`src/lib/validators.ts`)
- **Sonner** for toasts, **dnd-kit** for reordering
- **MQTT.js** browser client for realtime IoT topics
- Node MQTT publish support for server-side OTA trigger dispatch

## Route groups

- `(auth)` - `/login` (public)
- `(dashboard)` - `/dashboard`, `/editor`, `/editor/[mapId]`, `/dashboard/iot`, `/dashboard/programming` (auth-guarded by `src/middleware.ts`)
- `(display)` - `/map/[mapId]` (public, only when `is_published`; includes IoT read-only overlays + sensor card)
- API: `auth/[...nextauth]`, `maps`, `maps/[id]`, `maps/[id]/devices`, `ota/*`, `iot/register/*`, `iot/ota/ack`, `upload`, `files/[id]`

## Conventions

- Always run `npm run typecheck` and `npm run build` after substantive edits.
- All DB columns are `snake_case`; the app uses `camelCase`. Use the mappers in `src/lib/utils.ts` (`mapRowToCampusMap`, `mapRowToBuilding`) - never read raw rows in components.
- New building / map / IoT fields must be added in **all** of: SQL (`database/setup.sql` + idempotent `ALTER TABLE` in `scripts/setup-db.ts`), row + app types in `src/lib/utils.ts`/`src/types/index.ts`, Zod schemas, and API `INSERT/UPDATE` statements.
- IoT types are `light`, `water_valve`, and `temp_humidity`; enforce one `temp_humidity` sensor per map in API logic.
- OTA additions require schema + setup script + teardown + types/mappers + validators + API route parity. Firmware metadata lives in `firmware_builds`, device runtime OTA state lives on `iot_devices`, and push audit logs live in `ota_update_logs`.
- Uploads go to `./uploads/` (project root, not `public/`) and are served via `GET /api/files/[id]`.
- Use `next/image` with `unoptimized` for `/api/files/...` URLs.
